@node Race
@section Race
@cindex character race
@cindex race, character

There are seven available character races, from which you
must choose yout character's race.

@table @bullet
@item  Human
There really is nothing special about humans.
@item  Half-Orc
Half-Orcs receive a bonus point to their strength and
constitution, but a penality point to intelligence and
charisma.
@item  Half-Elf
Half-elves have infravisiton and limited (50 %) resistance
to charm and sleep spells.
@item  Elf
Elves have infravistion and full resistance to charm and
sleep spells. They have a  −2 bonus point THAC0 when using
bows and long swords. Finally, they have a receive a bonus
point to their dexterity, but a penalty point to their
constitution.
@item  Dwarf
Dwarves have infravision and full resistance to magic and
poison. They have a receive a bonus point to their
constituion, but a penalty point to their charisma and
dexterity.
@item  Halfling
Halflings have high (75 %) resistance to poison and magic,
and have −4 2 bonus point THAC0 when using slings. They
have a receive a bonus point to their dexterity, but a
penalty point to their strength.
@item  Gnome
Gnomes have infravision and full resistance to magic, both
protective and distructive magic, but only wizard spells.
They receive a bonus point to their intelligence, but a
penalty point to their wisdom.
@end table


@node Classes
@section Classes
@cindex character classes
@cindex classes, character

The character's class is the most significant attribute
that decides how the character is player. The classes
you can select depends on the character's race.

Non-humans can be multiclassed, this is, have the
characteristics of two or three classes as the same time,
the earned experience is distributed evenly among the
classes.

Humans can dual class, that is, to forfeit leveling the
current class and instead start on the second class.
A character can only dual class once, and level 4 or
higher is required.

There are nine available classes.

@table @bullet
@item  Fighter (F)
Can wield any weapon and any armour except robes.
Can have advanced weapon speciailisation.
Can receive multiple hit bonus.
@item  Ranger (R)
Can wield any weapon and any armour except robes.
Special abilities: Charm person/mammal, Stealth.
Must be of good alignment.
@item  Paladin (P)
Can wield any weapon and any armour except robes.
Special abilities: Lay on Hands, Turn Undead,
Protection from Evil, detect Evil.
Receive +2 bonus to all Saving throws,
Must maintain lawful good alignment.
@item  Thief (T)
Cannot be of lawful good alignment.
Very restricted with what armour they can wear and
with weapones they can wield.
@item  Bard (B)
Special abilties: Pick Pockets, Bard Songs, Spell Casting.
Have very high lore. Must be have partially neutral
alignment, that is not lawful/chaotic good/evil.
@item  Cleric (C)
Special abilties: Turn Undead.
@item  Druid (D)
Special abilties: Shape Change.
@item  Mage (M)
Can learn and memorise wizard spells.
Very restricted with what armour they can wear and with
weapones they can wield, however alone with sorcerers to
be able to wear robes.
@item  Sorcerer (S)
Cannot learn spells from scrolls, but learns new wizard
spells at level up, and do not need to memorise spells, but
have a limited amouts of spells that can be used per
spell-level until rested.
Very restricted with what armour they can wear and with
weapones they can wield, however alone with mages to be
able to wear robes.
@end table

Fighter, ranger and paladin is collectively known as
warrior. Thief and bard is collectively known as rogue.
Cleric and druid is collectively known as priest. And mage
and sorcerer is collectively known as wizard.

Bards, mages and sorcerers cannot perform magic will wearing
non-leather armour. This applies even to multiclassed and
dualclasses characters.

Humans can be of any class and are alone be able to be
paladins, and any race can be of the classes fighter, thief
(with the exception for half-orc), cleric, mage and
sorcerer. Additionally elf and half-elf can be rangers, and
for half-elf, also druid and bard. However gnomes cannot be
general mages, but only illusionists (I).

