@node Ability scores
@section Ability scores
@cindex charcter ability scores
@cindex ability scores, charcter

There are six ability scores.

@itemize @bullet
@item  Strength (Warrior)
@item  Constitution
@item  Dexterity (Thief)
@item  Intelligence (Wizard)
@item  Wisdom (Priest)
@item  Charisma (Druid, bard, paladin@footnote{Charisma lower limit +14 instead of +3 for paladins})
@end itemize

By default the lower bounds are 3 and the upper bounds are 18,
one of the factors that change this is the class. In the list
above, the classes inside brackets have +6 (9 instead of 3) on
their lower bound on the indicated ability.

The score of an each ability is determined by rolling three
six-sided dies and sum the values up. If the lower bound
is not satisified the value will be set to the lower bound.
Additionally fighters, rangers and paladins throw two
(ordered) ten-sided die that determines that extra value on
the strength if it is set to 18. The extra strength value is
0 for non-fighters and for fighters the first roll modulo 10
times 10 plus the second roll modulo 10, if this adds up to
0, then the value is instead 100. The strength 18 with 100 as
the extra is displayed as 18/00. During the character
creation you can rearrange the values and reroll the dice
until you are satisfied.


