The specialist mage classes are alternative to regular mage
class, they can memorise one extra spell per spell level
that they can normally use. They can however not learn, but
they can use directly from scroll, spells in their
opposition schools. With the exception for gnomes,
specialist mages cannot be multiclassed, but they can be
dualclassed from, but not towards.

@itemize @bullet
@item @b{Abjurer:} Specialises in protective magic.
@item @b{Conjurer:} Specialises in creating creatures and objects.
@item @b{Diviner:} Specialises in detection and divining magic.
@item @b{Enchanter:} Specialises in mind manipulation.
@item @b{Illusionist:} Specialises in creating illusions.
@item @b{Invoker:} Specialises in invocation magic.
@item @b{Necromancer:} Specialises in magic dealing with life and death.
@item @b{Transmuter:} Specialises in physical reality alteration.
@end itemize

Sorcerers, priests, rangers, paladins and bards cannot be
specialists.


