@node Spell properties
@section Spell properties
@cindex spell properties

@table @b
@item Range
@cindex range
The distance from the caster at which the spell effect
occurs or begins, in metres. If the range is zero, it can
only be used ont the caster himself; ‘Touch’ can use the
spell on others if he can physically touch them, which
requires a sucessful hit roll. These two special ranges
can be combinded, meaning that either can be utilied,
this is denoted ‘0/Touch’.

@item Duration
@cindex duration
How long the spell's effect lasts, ‘0’ indicates that the
effect has no time span. Spells with duraction can be
negated sometimes by potions or other spells, usally Dispel
magic will do the trick. Some spells have a variable
duration indicated by a die roll notation; for example
‘2D4+1 rounds’ means that two four-sided dice are thrown
and that the sum of the eyes, added by 1, is the number of
round that the spell's effect will last.

@item Casting time
@cindex casting time
The number of tenths of a round that is needed for the
spellcaster to cast the spell.

@item Area of effect
@cindex area of effect
Specifies which targets are affect by the spell, this can
incluce groups of creatures, hostality and radius.

@item Saving throw
@cindex saving throw
Specifies whether the target is allowed a saving throw, and
what the effect of a successful save whould be. The effect
can either be ‘negate’ which nullifies the magic, or ‘half’
which divided the damage by 2. ‘None’ denotes that no save
is allowed.
@end table



