@node Detecting secret doors
@section Detecting secret doors
@cindex detecting secret doors
@cindex secret doors, detecting

At any time a character has a chance to detect sectret doors
depending on his class and race. Wizards have an 5 % chance,
15 % for thieves and 10 % for clerics and fighters, 0 % for
others. Elf get an additional 20 % chance, dwarfs get 10 %
and halflings get 5 %.

Thieves' chance increase by as much as their change to find
traps when their find traps ability is on.


@node Lore
@section Lore
@cindex lore

Item can be either identified or unidentified. Unidentified
item can be identified by priests at temples at monetary
cost, by using a identify spell or by examining the item
if it has a lore value equal to or lower than the examining
character's lore.

As characters gain levels they gain lore.

@itemize @bullet
@item  @b{Bards} gain 10 lore rating per level.
@item  @b{Thieves} gain 3 lore rating per level.
@item  @b{Wizards} gain 3 lore rating per level.
@item  @b{Others} gain 1 lore rating per level.
@end itemize


