@node Morale
@section Morale
@cindex morale

Morale affects whether a creature fights or flees during a
battle. Creatures react differently to morale breaks and
have different breaking levels, some creatures use melée
attacks at high morale and ranged attacks at low morale.

Morale is positively influenced by having a charismatic
leader, the leader himself however is not influensed by
this. Morale is negatively influenced by having seeing
morale break in the party, especially from the leader,
and by seeing a party member killed or knocked unconscious.
In some cases morale is negatively influenced by spotting
a difficult foe.


@node Saving throws
@section Saving throws
@cindex saving throws

Saving throws measures a character's resistance to different
types of attacks. The chance of making a successful saving
throw improves as the character increases in level; it can
also be improved by protection spells. A saving throw may
reduce damage or prevent the effect of an attack entirely.

@itemize @bullet
@item  @b{Save versus breath weapon:}
Used when facing monsters with breath weapons,
particularly the powerful blast of a dragon.
@item  @b{Save versus death magic, paralyzation, or poison:}
Used when a character is affected by a paralyzing attack,
poison or magic that otherwise kill the character outright.
@item  @b{Save versus petrification or polymorph:}
Used when a character is petrified or polymorphed.
@item  @b{Save versus rod, staff, or wand:}
Provided that another save of higher priority is not used,
this is used when affected by magical rods, staffs or wands.
@item  @b{Save versus spell:}
Provided that no other saving throw is specified, this is
used when a character attempts to resist the effects of
magic or attacks that cannot be classified in any other way.
@end itemize



