@cindex shape change, druidic

Level 8 and higher druids can transform into three different
animals, each once per day. Druids can transform into brown
bear, black bear, or wolf, perhaps with increased hit point,
movement rate and damage.


@node Infravision
@section Infravision
@cindex infravision

Infravision allows you to see heat and hence warm blooded
creatures in the dark more clearly. Undead or cold blooded
creatures are not affected by infravision.


@node Lay on hands
@section Lay on hands
@cindex lay on hands

Paladins can heal themself and others by laying their hands
upon the target to heal. The target is healed by 2 hit
points per experience level of the healer. Paladins can
use this ability once per sleep.


@node Protection from evil
@section Protection from evil
@cindex Protection from evil

This spell create a 0,3 m radius magical barrier around the
recipient, that moves with the recipient.

All attackes made by evil and evilly enchanted creatures
agains the protected character receive a penalty of −2 to
each attack roll. Additionally any saving throws made by
the protected character caused by such attacks receive a
+2 bonus.


@node Turning undead
@section Turning undead
@cindex turning undead
@cindex undead, turning

Clerics and paladins have the ability to turn undead. This
ability lets the deity manifest a portion of its power
through a mortal vessel that does not assure sucess.
Evil undead creatures can lose morale and run away. If the
deity's power is channeled through a good aligned clerics,
the undead can be destroyed outright. Evil clerics can
somtimes gain control over the undead.



