@node Effects of fatigue
@section Effects of fatigue
@cindex effects of fatigue
@cindex fatigue

A character can continue to operate at peak efficiency for
24 hours game time, after which the character receieves a
−1 luck penalty evety fourth hour. −1 luck means that every
roll (die) value is decrease by one, the value can however
not go below 1. If a character do not spell for five days
he may at any time fall unconscious.

As soon as the character has rested for 8 hours all
penalties will be removed, spells will be rememorised.
During spell the character will heal, the heal rate can be
increased by renting a room at an in, the higher quality
the grater the rate will be.


@node Effects of encumbrance
@section Effects of encumbrance
@cindex effects of encumbrance
@cindex encumbrance

How much a character can carry depends on the characters
strength. If this limit is exceeded the character will move
at half rate, positive speed effects from magic and items
will be not have any effect while a character is encumbered.
If the limit is exceeded too much the character will not
be able to move at all.


@node Effects of intoxication
@section Effects of intoxication
@cindex effects of intoxication
@cindex intoxication

Inns serve a variety of intoxicants; drinking to excess will
impair yout combat skill but improve your morale. The effects
of intoxicants wear off by time. Your morale is increased as
much as your luck is decreased when drinking.

The about you can drink before becoming intoxicated depends
on your constitution. Characters with 3 or less in constitution
will find them self drunk after one pony.


