We you assign score to abilities you will have a number of
score points to assign. There will always be a lower limit
for each abilities, and sometimes there is a maximum.

You can use the @kbd{up} and @kbd{down} arrows, or
@kbd{enter} instead of the @kbd{down} arrows, to navigate,
the curreny line is marked in bright blue. Use the
@kbd{left} and @kbd{right} arrows to remove and add score
points, respectively.

At any time you can use the @kbd{S} key to store the current
assignment and @kbd{R} to restore the last stored
assignments. When you assign strenght, constitution, et
cetera, the points are decided by rolling dices, meaning
that the number of assignable points (that are automatically
pre-assigned) is random. In this can use @kbd{C-r}
@footnote{@kbd{C-} means that Control is held down.}
to reroll can get new scores.

When you are done, press @kbd{D}, if you want to abort and
redo the last action you can press @kbd{C-g}.


