@cindex multiselection menus
@cindex menus, multiselection

Multiselection menus are menu where you can check which
attributes want, and have a fixed number of attributes
that most be selected. Each attributes can be selected once,
when selected, a bright green `X' is visible left of it.

You can use the @kbd{up} and @kbd{down} arrows, or
@kbd{enter} instead of the @kbd{down} arrows, to navigate,
the curreny line is marked in bright blue. Use the
@kbd{left} and @kbd{right} arrows to unselect and select,
respectively. @kbd{spacebar} can used to toggle selection.

When you are done, press @kbd{D}, if you want to abort and
redo the last action you can press @kbd{C-g}.


