@node Dialogues
@section Dialogues
@cindex dialogues
@cindex input, dialogues

Dialogues are one of the major parts of the game. Caution,
depending on the game senario low intelligence, may cause
a character to not be able to speak properly.

You can walk a ways from a dialog by pressing @kbd{C-g},
otherwise you press @kbd{enter}, @kbd{spacebar} or the
@kbd{right} arrow key. Often, but not always, you can
reply, in this case, you select a reply and press
@kbd{enter}, @kbd{spacebar} or the @kbd{right} arrow key.
Use the @kbd{up} and @kbd{down} arrow keys to navigate,
or use the number in front of the reply to select it
directly without having to press @kbd{enter},
@kbd{spacebar} or the @kbd{right} arrow key.

If the dialogue have been obstructed by printk or something
similar, you can press @kbd{C-l} to redraw the dialogue.


@node Starting the game
@section Starting the game
@cindex starting the game
@cindex input, starting the game

When you start the game will are asked for a game senario.
Use the @kbd{up} and @kbd{down} arrow keys to navigate and
press @kbd{enter}, @kbd{spacebar} or the @kbd{right} arrow
key. You can also the number, or letter, in front of the
senario you want to play.

You can press @kbd{C-g} to exit.

When you start playing you are, unless you play a weird
senario, welcomed by a prologue, these are, like chapter
introductions and books, navigated with the arrow keys,
@kbd{page up}(@kbd{prior}) and @kbd{page down}(@kbd{next}).
To continue, press @kbd{C-c}, @kbd{C-d}, @kbd{C-g}, @kbd{q}
or @kbd{w}.

If the text have been obstructed by printk or something
similar, you can press @kbd{C-l} to redraw the text.


