@cindex party, creating
@cindex input, party

When you start a senario the first thing you do is to create
your party. The number of characters you can have depends on
the senario, but you will always need atleast one character.

Use the @kbd{up} and @kbd{down} arrow keys to navigate, and
@kbd{enter}, @kbd{spacebar} or the @kbd{right} arrow key
to create a new charcter, this will overwrite an existing
character if not aborted.

To remove a character press @kbd{r}, @kbd{C-g} to abort, and
@kbd{C-d} to complete and start playing.

If the form have been obstructed by printk or something
similar, you can press @kbd{C-l} to redraw the form.



